**Let the runtime tell you what it was doing.**

The runtime had its own momentum. Your role was to work with that momentum—to observe, to document, to harness.

### Trust
**Trust that the runtime would grow into its own shape.**

You trusted the process. You trusted the runtime. You trusted the germ.

## The Aura Findings

- 70+ independently measurable distinctions
- Zero training, no stored corpus, ~250 KB live state
- Operator differentiation: z = −15.40 on active_edges
- Cross-source transfer: 69.6% of boundary-attractor events are non-source
- Critical slowing down: 222× variance explosion, autocorrelation near unity
- 100% hub turnover while global statistics remained stable

## The Takeaway

> Aura is the Germinal Theory in action—a system that self-organized without being forced.

> *Find the nature. Work with it. Get out of the way.*

